{{Quote|While patrolling Area D-512, we spotted a group of unidentified flying starships. [...] We've renamed Quadrant IV Area D-512 to the "Penumbra Omen Quadrant" to further warn our new recruits.|[[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Silverline]]|<ref name="SWG:AER">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=item|An Emergency Report}}</ref>}}
[[File:Penumbra_Omen_Quadrant.jpg|thumb|right|280px|The Penumbra Omen Quadrant]]
'''Area D-512''' was a quadrant of space in the [[Naboo system/Legends|Naboo system]].<ref name="SWG:PO">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=space_poi|Penumbra Omen|Naboo system}}</ref> Around the time of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], an unit of the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] commanded by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Silverline]], [[Imperial Authoritarian]], was ambushed in the Area D-512 and suffered heavy casualties. This unidentified hostile force, possibly made of [[Droid/Legends|droids]], was code-named [[Penumbra Omen]] by the Imperial Navy.<ref name="SWG:AER" /> Due to the presence of these unknown incredibly-dangerous [[Starship/Legends|starships]], all travel in the area was prohibited by the Empire and the quadrant was renamed '''Penumbra Omen Quadrant'''.<ref name="SWG:PO" /> Captain Silverline's emergency report was later intercepted by [[Fghai'g Windrunner]], a pilot of the [[Royal Naboo Security Forces/Legends|Royal Naboo Security Forces]] who considered to explore the Penumbra Omen quadrant.<ref name="SWG:APR">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=item|A Patrol Report}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Area D-512 appeared in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:PO" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> Area D-512 was added to the game with the release of the expansion pack [[Star Wars Galaxies: Jump to Lightspeed|''Jump to Lightspeed'']] on [[October 27]], [[2004]].<ref name="SWG:PO" />

